Name: DART_Parameters
Description: The DART_Parameters class is the superclass containing all DART mission data dictionary classes.

Name: mission_phase
Description: The mission_phase identifies the time period within the mission.

Name: approach
Description: The approach phase begins begins when the Didymos system is first acquired by DRACO, ~30 days before impact, and extends until the terminal phase begins. During this phase, DRACO acquires a long-range suite of observations where the Didymos system is mostly not resolvable. Light curve information complementary to ground-based observations will be extracted from these images.

Name: commissioning
Description: The commissioning phase lasts for TBD days after launch. Images acquired during this phase include calibrations and functional testing for DRACO to ensure proper operations.

Name: cruise
Description: The cruise phase begins after the commissioning phase and runs until the beginning of teh approach phase. Images acquired during this phase are used for several purposes, including for Optical navigation (OpNav), testing of SMART Nav algorithms, and star calibrations to characterize distortion and responsivity.

Name: final
Description: The final phase comprises the last ~4 min of the DART mission. During this phase, all DRACO images will be devoted to characterization of Dimorphos, as autonomous navingation will have been completed. In the baseline trajectory at ~20s (TBR after launch) prior to impact, DRACO achieves its requirement to image Dimorphos at a pixel scale of 66 cm. Higher resolution images will continue to be acquired in the final seconds of DART spacecraft operations, which end upon impact.

Name: prelaunch
Description: The prelaunch phase refers to the period of software development and testing of the data processing pipeline, before launch. Data products generated during this phase include calibration files created during the ground testing of the instrument as well as data products created for peer review.

Name: terminal
Description: The terminal phase begins with the initiation of DART's autonomous navigation, ~4 h prior to impact, and extends until the final phase begins. During this phase, the separation between Didymos and Dimorphos can be resolved, and DRACO images support both autonomous navigation (via Smart Nav algorithms) and characterization of Didymos and Dimorphos. The final image to contain both members of the system will be acquired ~4 minutes before impact, at a scale of ~7m. By the end of this phase, images will be obtained of Dimorphos that have a 2 x 2 binned pixel scale of ~3.5m.

Name: Time
Description: The Time class contains metadata describing different time components associated with the DART mission.

Name: acquisition_time
Description: DRACO image time of validity (TOV) in integer seconds, in spacecraft clock notation. This is the time for which the GNC attitude data is valid. See the DRACO SIS for calculation of this value.

Name: soc_acquisition_time
Description: DRACO image time of validity calculated by the SOC based on FPE_SEC and FPE_SBSS in the fits header. Represented as ascii integers in "sec:subsecond_ticks" where "sec" is the spacecraft clock counter in whole seconds since epoch and "subsecond_ticks" are in spacecraft clock subsecond clock ticks. Each tick represents 1/50,000 second. Example: "298271898:2345"

Name: liciacube_sclk_image_time
Description: Start of image capture time in spacecraft clock notation. Numeric number preceding the decimal point is integer seconds. Numeric number after the decimal point is subsecond clock ticks, where each tick represents TBD microseconds.

Name: correct_image_time
Description: LICIACube keyword containing the UTC Time at mid exposure as measured from the effective time of aquisition. This is the reference time used to generate the SPICE derived geometry values in the LICIACube fits header.

Name: DRACO_Instrument_Attributes
Description: The DRACO_Instrument_Attributes class contains metadata associated with the DRACO Instrument.

Name: imaging_mode
Description: The imaging_mode defines the shutter readout mode of the DRACO detector.

Name: GLOBAL
Description: In global shutter readout mode the entire detector integrates over the same time period. Global shutter images will have higher noise relative to rolling shutter images, but no spatial distortion beyond that caused by the optics (less than or equal to 0.1%).

Name: ROLLING
Description: In rolling shutter mode each row of the detector integrates over the same amount of time, but the exact moment in time captured by each line is different (i.e., each line begins integrating by one line time after the previous line).

Name: gain
Description: Defines the detector gain setting used. The container class identifies whether this is for the DRACO, LUKE, or LEIA detectors.

Name: 10X
Description: High gain amplification 10X.

Name: 1X
Description: Low gain amplification 1X.

Name: 2X
Description: Low gain amplification 2X.

Name: 30X
Description: High gain amplification 30X.

Name: bad_image
Description: Identifies image whose image data and FPE metadata are not reliable and should not be used for analysis.

Name: false
Description: This is not a bad image. Can be used for analysis.

Name: true
Description: This is a bad image. Should not be used for analysis

Name: observation_type
Description: Describes the purpose for which the image was taken.

Name: lineread
Description: Defines the time it takes to readout a single line of the detector in microsec/line.

Name: pix_delay
Description: Delay between sequential pixels in line in nanoseconds.

Name: exposure_time
Description: Image exposure time in seconds.

Name: test_pattern
Description: If present it describes the test pattern in the image. If there is no test pattern then this keyword will not appear in the label.

Name: DYNAHORZ
Description: The image contains a dynamic horizontal gradient test pattern. It is dynamic in the sense that the pixel values created by this test pattern vary from image to image.

Name: FLAT
Description: The image contains a uniform gray image.

Name: STATHORZ
Description: The image contains a static horizontal gradient test pattern.

Name: TWOBOX
Description: The image contains a two-box test pattern.

Name: binning
Description: Identifies whether pixel binning was applied to generate the image.

Name: OFF
Description: Binning not applied

Name: ON
Description: Binning applied

Name: window2_x_start
Description: Starting column of windowed image data with respect to a 1024 x 1025 image array, where the top row of the array is the header row containing metadata associated with the image. Upper left hand corner is coordinate 0,0. Set to -1 if windowing is not applied.

Name: window2_y_start
Description: Starting row of windowed image data with respect to a 1024 x 1025 image array, where the top row of the array is the header row containing metadata associated with the image. Upper left hand corner is coordinate 0,0. Set to -1 if windowing is not applied.

Name: window2_x_end
Description: Ending column of windowed image data with respect to a 1024 x 1025 image array, where the top row of the array is the header row containing metadata associated with the image. Upper left hand corner is coordinate 0,0. Set to -1 if windowing is not applied.

Name: window2_y_end
Description: Ending row of windowed image data with respect to a 1024 x 1025 image array, where the top row of the array is the header row containing metadata associated with the image. Upper left hand corner is coordinate 0,0. Set to -1 if windowing is not applied.

Name: onboard_cal
Description: Defines whether calibration table was applied to the DRACO image onboard the DART spacecraft prior to downlink.

Name: OFF
Description: Onboard calibration not applied

Name: ON
Description: Onboard calibration applied

Name: calibration_file
Description: Name of calibration table file provided by SMART Nav to the spacecraft for use when onboard calibration is applied. Data values from this file are added back to the downloaded image if applied to the image on board. The file is stored on-board as a .mat file, but the same data values are archived in the DRACO Calibrated Data Collection as a .fits file. The archived filename is the same as the base filename shown here with the '.fits' extension.

Name: badpix_invalidation_mode
Description: Flags whether bad pixels identified by the on-board bad pixel map are invalidated by SMARTNAV. When invalidated the pixels in the raw image are set to the SNAVFLAG value in the raw fits header.

Name: BYPASS
Description: Bad pixel map is not used to invalidate pixels.

Name: USE
Description: Bad pixels identified by bad pixel map are invalidated by SMARTNAV

Name: detector1_temp
Description: DRACO detector temperature sensor 1.

Name: detector2_temp
Description: DRACO detector temperature sensor 2.

Name: fpe_temp
Description: DRACO FPE board temperature.

Name: current_18vd_supply
Description: Current for detector 1.8VD supply.

Name: current_33va_supply
Description: Current for detector 3.3VA supply.

Name: current_33vd_supply
Description: Current for detector 3.3VD supply.

Name: current_analog_reset_supply
Description: Current for detector analog reset supply.

Name: test_temp
Description: Nominal temperature for the test sequence used to generate the data product. Reported by the calibration files, i.e. flat fields, bias, and dark images.

Name: DRACO_Data_Processing_Information
Description: The DRACO_data_processing_information class contains metadata describing the processing steps performed on the image. The processing steps are listed in the same order executed by the data processing pipeline

Name: undo_onboard_cal
Description: Indicates whether on-board calibration table was undone, ie. by adding it back to the image. NA if onboard_cal table was not applied to the image.

Name: NA
Description: Onboard calibration not applied to the image

Name: UNDONE
Description: Removed the onboard calibration table

Name: bias_subtraction
Description: Indicates whether bias subtraction step was done. If performed, then refer to the REFBIAS keyword in the fits header for the name of the bias file used. This file is also archived in the DRACO Calibrated Data Collection.

Name: PERFORM
Description: performed bias subtraction

Name: SKIP
Description: skipped bias subtraction

Name: dark_subtraction
Description: Indicates whether dark subtraction step was done. If performed then refer to the REFDARK1 and REFDARK2 keywords in the fits header for the names of the dark files used. These files are also archived in the DRACO Calibrated Data Collection. Also refer to the DRACO calibration pipeline description document to see how the two files are utilized to interpolate temperature dependent dark currents.

Name: PERFORM
Description: performed dark subtraction

Name: SKIP
Description: skipped dark subtraction

Name: flatfield
Description: Indicates whether flat field was applied. If performed then refer to the REFFLAT keyword in the fits header for the names of the flat field files used. This file is also archived in the DRACO Calibrated Data Collection.

Name: PERFORM
Description: applied flat field

Name: SKIP
Description: skipped flat field application

Name: radiance_conversion
Description: Indicates whether conversion to radiance was applied. If performed then refer to the the DRACO calibration pipeline description document for the steps performed to convert pixel values to electrons then from electrons to radiance. The lookup table used to convert pixel values to electrons is stored in the LUPTABLE keyword in the fits header along with the photometric keyword RDIDYMOS. The lookup table file is also archived in the DRACO Calibrated Data Collection.

Name: PERFORM
Description: converted pixels to radiance values

Name: SKIP
Description: skipped conversion to radiance

Name: ioverf_conversion
Description: Indicates whether conversion to I/F was applied. If performed then refer to the DRACO calibraiton pipeline description document for the steps performed to convert pixel values to I/F. The F_SUN622 keyword in the fits header contains the solar flux at 622nm (the DRACO pivot wavelength) as well as the PHDIST and SHDIST keywords for the heliocentric distance to the primary and secondary bodies respectively.

Name: PERFORM
Description: converted pixels to I/F values

Name: SKIP
Description: skipped conversion to I/F
